{"data":{},"content":[{"data":{},"content":[{"data":{},"marks":[],"value":"Choi Jihoon is a utility backline damage dealer who assists the team from afar with various effects. Choi Jihoon is notable in that he applies a 100% uptime skill seal + blind with his basic attacks, which can lock down frontline targets and greatly hinder their cast times. Choi Jihoon also has limited backline access through his sure-crit enhanced basic, which targets the furthest enemy in range. Unfortunately, Choi Jihoon struggles to find a real niche for himself.","nodeType":"text"}],"nodeType":"paragraph"},{"data":{},"content":[{"data":{},"marks":[],"value":"In PVE, Choi Jihoon’s skill seal doesn’t apply to bosses, severely limiting the situations in which his kit may provide value to the point where he is never realistically a consideration. For all scenarios, there exist more effective alternatives for the role (e.g. Awakened Lyudmila).","nodeType":"text"}],"nodeType":"paragraph"},{"data":{},"content":[{"data":{},"marks":[],"value":"In PVP, Choi Jihoon’s “100% uptime” skill seal needs to be constantly reapplied via his basic attacks. The skill seal falls off the moment he is disrupted or the shot is intercepted by another unit. As a backline access unit, Choi Jihoon cannot hold a candle to dedicated disruption units who commit harder and achieve more (e.g. Rearm Eujin, Rearm Sylvia). ","nodeType":"text"}],"nodeType":"paragraph"},{"data":{},"content":[{"data":{},"marks":[],"value":"Above all, Choi Jihoon’s personal damage output is anemic and without survivability tools himself it is frequently the case that he dies to the slightest pressure without achieving anything.","nodeType":"text"}],"nodeType":"paragraph"},{"data":{},"content":[{"data":{},"marks":[],"value":"
